\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Natural Language Generation (NLG) is a subfield of artificial intelligence that focuses on generating human-like text based on data inputs. NLG systems are used to create reports, summaries, and personalized content in various industries, including finance, healthcare, and marketing. Techniques such as template-based generation, rule-based systems, and machine learning models enable NLG to produce coherent and contextually relevant text. Applications of NLG include automated journalism, chatbots, and data-driven storytelling. The advancement of NLG technology is driven by improvements in natural language processing, deep learning, and computational linguistics.}